{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AkNcW68qYEkazGpXYEjz8u","type":"tool_result","content":"kv.snapshot.external_files.enabled\tfalse\tb\tf\tenables sending external files as metadata during a snapshot\tfalse\tdefault\nkv.snapshot.ingest_as_write_threshold\t100 KiB\tz\tf\tsize below which a range snapshot ingestion will be performed as a normal write\t100 KiB\tdefault\nkv.snapshot_delegation.max_delegation_attempts\t1\ti\tf\tthe max number of delegates to attempt for sending snapshots, before falling back to sending from the leaseholder. set to 0 to disable delegated snapshots.\t1\tdefault\nkv.snapshot_delegations.queue_limit\t3\ti\tf\tthe max requests a delegate can queue before rejecting an additional delegation request. set to -1 to allow unlimited requests\t3\tdefault\nkv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate\t1.0 MiB\tz\tt\tthe rate limit (bytes/sec) to use for rebalance and upreplication snapshots\t32 MiB\toverride\nkv.snapshot_receiver.excise.enabled\ttrue\tb\tt\tset to false to disable excises in place of range deletions for KV snapshots\ttrue\tdefault\nkv.snapshot_receiver.reservation_queue_timeout_fraction\t0.4\tf\tf\tthe fraction of a snapshot's total timeout that it is allowed to spend queued on the receiver waiting for a reservation\t0.4\tdefault\nkv.snapshot_sender.batch_size\t256 KiB\tz\tf\tsize of key-value batches sent over the network during snapshots\t256 KiB\tdefault\nkv.snapshot_sst.sync_size\t512 KiB\tz\tf\tthreshold after which snapshot SST writes must fsync\t512 KiB\tdefault\nsql.defaults.cost_scans_with_default_col_size.enabled\tfalse\tb\tt\tsetting to true uses the same size for all columns to compute scan cost\tfalse\tdefault\nsql.defaults.datestyle\tiso, mdy\te\tt\tdefault value for DateStyle session setting [iso, mdy = 0, iso, dmy = 1, iso, ymd = 2]\tiso, mdy\tdefault\nsql.defaults.default_hash_sharded_index_bucket_count\t16\ti\tt\tused as bucket count if bucket count is not specified in hash sharded index definition\t16\tdefault\nsql.defaults.default_int_size\t8\ti\tt\tthe size, in bytes, of an INT type\t8\tdefault\nsql.defaults.disallow_full_table_scans.enabled\tfalse\tb\tt\tsetting to true rejects queries that have planned a full table scan\tfalse\tdefault\nsql.defaults.distsql\tauto\te\tt\tdefault distributed SQL execution mode [off = 0, auto = 1, on = 2, always = 3]\tauto\tdefault\nsql.defaults.experimental_alter_column_type.enabled\tfalse\tb\tt\tdefault value for experimental_alter_column_type session setting; enables the use of ALTER COLUMN TYPE for general conversions\tfalse\tdefault\nsql.defaults.experimental_auto_rehoming.enabled\tfalse\tb\tf\tdefault value for experimental_enable_auto_rehoming; allows for rows in REGIONAL BY ROW tables to be auto-rehomed on UPDATE\tfalse\tdefault\nsql.defaults.experimental_computed_column_rewrites\t\ts\tf\tallows rewriting computed column expressions in CREATE TABLE and ALTER TABLE statements; the format is: '(before expression) -> (after expression) [, (before expression) -> (after expression) ...]'\t\tdefault\nsql.defaults.experimental_distsql_planning\toff\te\tt\tdefault experimental_distsql_planning mode; enables experimental opt-driven DistSQL planning [off = 0, on = 1]\toff\tdefault\nsql.defaults.experimental_enable_unique_without_index_constraints.enabled\tfalse\tb\tt\tdefault value for experimental_enable_unique_without_index_constraints session setting;disables unique without index constraints by default\tfalse\tdefault\nsql.defaults.experimental_implicit_column_partitioning.enabled\tfalse\tb\tt\tdefault value for experimental_enable_temp_tables; allows for the use of implicit column partitioning\tfalse\tdefault\nsql.defaults.experimental_temporary_tables.enabled\tfalse\tb\tt\tdefault value for experimental_enable_temp_tables; allows for use of temporary tables by default\tfalse\tdefault\nsql.defaults.foreign_key_cascades_limit\t10000\ti\tt\tdefault value for foreign_key_cascades_limit session setting; limits the number of cascading operations that run as part of a single query\t10000\tdefault\nsql.defaults.idle_in_session_timeout\t0s\td\tt\tdefault value for the idle_in_session_timeout; default value for the idle_in_session_timeout session setting; controls the duration a session is permitted to idle before the session is terminated; if set to 0, there is no timeout\t0s\tdefault\nsql.defaults.idle_in_transaction_session_timeout\t0s\td\tt\tdefault value for the idle_in_transaction_session_timeout; controls the duration a session is permitted to idle in a transaction before the session is terminated; if set to 0, there is no timeout\t0s\tdefault\nsql.defaults.implicit_select_for_update.enabled\ttrue\tb\tt\tdefault value for enable_implicit_select_for_update session setting; enables FOR UPDATE locking during the row-fetch phase of mutation statements\ttrue\tdefault\nsql.defaults.insert_fast_path.enabled\ttrue\tb\tt\tdefault value for enable_insert_fast_path session setting; enables a specialized insert path\ttrue\tdefault\nsql.defaults.intervalstyle\tpostgres\te\tt\tdefault value for IntervalStyle session setting [postgres = 0, iso_8601 = 1, sql_standard = 2]\tpostgres\tdefault\nsql.defaults.large_full_scan_rows\t1000\tf\tt\tdefault value for large_full_scan_rows session setting which determines the maximum table size allowed for a full scan when disallow_full_table_scans is set to true\t1000\tdefault\nsql.defaults.locality_optimized_partitioned_index_scan.enabled\ttrue\tb\tt\tdefault value for locality_optimized_partitioned_index_scan session setting; enables searching for rows in the current region before searching remote regions\ttrue\tdefault","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0d1c6193-c849-4a56-bf65-e2d37ad520cd","uuid":"79f8356f-121d-4cdf-80c5-31c93b4a6cae","timestamp":"2026-06-14T06:13:46.785Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"kv.snapshot.external_files.enabled\tfalse\tb\tf\tenables sending external files as metadata during a snapshot\tfalse\tdefault\